Messages of support and condolences continue to pour in after the death of Dinilesizwe Sobukwe. The son of former Pan Africanist Congress of Azania (PAC) leader, Robert Sobukwe, died in a Port Elizabeth Hospital after a short illness. His death has been described as a great loss to the Eastern Cape and people from his home town Graaff Reinet. He was 63-years-old. Reverend Louis Williams from the Methodist Church says they are ready to support the family. “It is with great sadness that we came to know of the passing of Dini and from the side of the Methodist Church, we offer our support to the family and we will be guided by the family as to what the funeral arrangements will be.” Click below for more on the story: 